//eucalyptus.atlassian.net/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=14811&avatarType=issuetype","name":"New Feature","subtask":false,"avatarId":14811}}}}],"assignee":null,"updated":"2015-05-08T17:15:21.338-0500","status":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/status/6","description":"The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png","name":"Closed","id":"6","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"components":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10201","id":"10201","name":"AWS Compatibility"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/11504","id":"11504","name":"EC2"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"customfield_13000":null,"description":"*Assessment*\r\n\r\nOn Eucalyptus 4.0, the result of [ImportInstance|http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/APIReference/ApiReference-query-ImportInstance.html] is a running EBS-backed instance.  This differs from AWS.  This is important because it keeps users from attaching volumes to a stopped EBS-backed instance, and then starting the instance - which is a [use case mentioned by AWS|http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/VMImportPrerequisites.html#vmimport-limitations].  Since [ImportInstance|http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/APIReference/ApiReference-query-ImportInstance.html] doesn't support images with multiple disks, this is a way to allow users to import images that were created with multiple disks (i.e. a disk for /boot, disk for /, etc.):\r\n\r\n{quote}\r\nMake sure your VM only uses a single disk. Importing a VM with more than one disk is not supported. For Linux VMs, /boot and / can be located in different partitions, but they need to be on the same disk.\r\n.....\r\nWe suggest that you import the VM with only the boot volume, and import any additional disks using the [ec2-import-volume|http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/CommandLineReference/ApiReference-cmd-ImportVolume.html] command. After the ImportInstance task is complete, use the [ec2-attach-volume|http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/CommandLineReference/ApiReference-cmd-AttachVolume.html] command to associate the additional volumes with your instance.  \r\n{quote}\r\n\r\n*Pertinent Data*\r\n\r\nA use case here would be [importing a VMware VM that was created with two disks|http://serverfault.com/questions/442973/import-a-vmware-virtual-machine-with-two-disks-into-amazon-aws]. This would help users migrate from VMware to KVM easier using Eucalyptus.\r\n\r\n*Signs*\r\n\r\n* euca-describe-instances of imported instance on Eucalyptus 4.0:\r\n{code}\r\n[root@odc-f-13 ~]# euca-describe-conversion-tasks --region account1-user01@\r\nTaskType\tIMPORTINSTANCE\tTaskId\timport-i-c3971fb1\tExpirationTime\tMon Jun 16 17:45:32 PDT 2014\tStatus\tactive\tStatusMessage\tLaunching instance\r\nDISKIMAGE\tDiskImageFormat\tRAW\tDiskImageSize\t2361393152\tVolumeId\tvol-D17E9A0A\tVolumeSize\t3\tAvailabilityZone\tViciousLiesAndDangerousRumors\tApproximateBytesConverted\t2361393152\tStatus\tcompleted\r\n\r\n[root@odc-f-13 ~]# euca-describe-instances i-F68C2CE5 --region account1-user01@\r\nRESERVATION\tr-108AB082\t408396244283\tdefault\r\nINSTANCE\ti-F68C2CE5\temi-B13585D7\teuca-10-104-6-236.bigboi.acme.eucalyptus-systems.com\teuca-172-18-238-146.bigboi.internal\trunning\t\t0\t\tm1.medium\t2014-06-10T00:55:22.378Z\tViciousLiesAndDangerousRumors\t\t\t\tmonitoring-disabled\t10.104.6.236\t172.18.238.14\t\t\tebs\t\t\t\t\thvm\t\t\tsg-A5133B59\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n*on AWS*\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n[root@odc-f-13 ~]# ec2-describe-conversion-tasks -W XXXXXXXXX -O XXXXXXXXX --url https://ec2.us-west-1.amazonaws.com\r\n\r\nTaskType\tIMPORTINSTANCE\tTaskId\timport-i-fgepm81f\tExpirationTime\t2014-06-16T17:12:16Z\tStatus\tcompleted\tInstanceID\ti-5821e206\r\nDISKIMAGE\tDiskImageFormat\tRAW\tDiskImageSize\t2361393152\tVolumeId\tvol-7d82137d\tVolumeSize\t3\tAvailabilityZone\tus-west-1c\tApproximateBytesConverted\t1216348160\tStatus\tcompleted\r\n\r\n[root@odc-f-13 ~]# ec2-describe-instances --url https://ec2.us-west-1.amazonaws.com -W XXXXXXXXXXX -O XXXXXXXXXXX\r\nRESERVATION\tr-e6eef3b9\t986451091583\tdefault\r\nINSTANCE\ti-5821e206\tami-26141363\t\t\tstopped\t\t0\t\tm3.medium\t2014-06-09T17:12:15+0000\tus-west-1c\t\t\t\tmonitoring-disabled\t\t\t\t\tebs\t\t\t\t\thvm\txen\t\tsg-65e2eb20\tdefault\tfalse\r\n\r\nBLOCKDEVICE\t/dev/sda1\tvol-7d82137d\t2014-06-09T17:40:44.000Z\tfalse\r\n{code}","customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"attachment":[],"summary":"Instance Created from ImportInstance Goes To Running State on Eucalyptus","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=hspencer","name":"hspencer","key":"hspencer","accountId":"557058:4a3a93bc-21f8-4658-9f5b-9cb484c910a7","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/ea43d7b9d5b27468a749f9bd25650176?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dhspencer%26avatarId%3D10407%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/ea43d7b9d5b27468a749f9bd25650176?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dhspencer%26avatarId%3D10407%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/ea43d7b9d5b27468a749f9bd25650176?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dhspencer%26avatarId%3D10407%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/ea43d7b9d5b27468a749f9bd25650176?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dhspencer%26avatarId%3D104